history.content:
EE 120 doesn't require much prerequisite knowledge beyond 1D calculus and familiarity with complex numbers. When Babak last taught, there were three in-class midterms, three in-class quizzes (one week before the midterms), six problem sets (approximately two weeks apart), and some Jupyter labs.

Low-workload class as long as you keep up with the material. Given your background, I imagine most of the topics wouldn't be too conceptually difficult.

Hi, I'm trying to decide on classes for Spring 2020? How doable would EE120 be with CS189? I have taken stat 140 and stat 135 as background for 189. I'm not sure on the workload for ee120. Can anyone comment on how much time the class is and how difficult the content is?
